dct_title_s: Wabash River and Valley from Terre Haute, Ind. to mouth, in 13 charts, 1914
dct_description_sm: Surveyed and mapped under the direction of the United States engineer officer, Louisville, Ky. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings. "Revisions made July 1931." "The survey of the river proper was begun July 25, and completed December 31, 1911. The valley survey began January 15, and was completed September 10, 1912. Mapping in 1913." 1 map on 13 sheets, photocopy.
Dimensions: sheets 92 x 122 cm; Scale: Approximately 1:24,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army. Corps of Engineers
dct_publisher_sm: United States. Army. Corps of Engineers. Louisville District
